This paper discusses data quality in the context of the Semantic Web, which involves data integration, decision-making, and planning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper's focus on industrial experience suggests that it may also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
